      "side": 1,
      "message": "This is not accurate.\n\nThe key factor for online reindexing compatibility is the Lucene major version used by the involved Gerrit releases, not downgrade considerations.\n\nLucene only guarantees backward compatibility for index formats of the current and previous (N-1) major versions. This means a newer Lucene version can only read indexes created by the previous major Lucene version.\n\nFor example:\n\n* Gerrit 3.12 → Lucene 10.x\n* Gerrit 3.11 / 3.10 → Lucene 9.x\n* Gerrit 3.9 → Lucene 8.x\n\nAs a result:\n\n* Online Upgrade 3.10 → 3.12 works (Lucene 9 → 10, supported N-1)\n* Online Upgrade 3.9 → 3.12 does not work (Lucene 8 → 10, N-2, not supported)\n\nSo the limitation is not about downgrade scenarios, but about Lucene’s index format compatibility across major versions.",
